The country has also recorded 72 new COVID-19 related fatalities on Monday. This brings the total number of deaths to 55 874. In a statement, Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize says most of the new deaths were recorded in the Free State. “Regrettably, we report 72 more COVID-19 related deaths: Eastern Cape 6, Free State 21, Gauteng 7, Kwa-Zulu Natal 0, Limpopo 13, Mpumalanga 6, North West 0, Northern Cape 6 and Western Cape 13,” says Dr Mkhize. Recoveries stand at 1 541 250. The cumulative number of tests conducted to date is 11 378 282. As of today, the total number of confirmed #COVID19 cases is 1 637 848 the total number of deaths is 55 874 the total number of recoveries is 1 541 250 and the total number of vaccines administered is 651 628. pic.twitter.com/dfuUG5yTCJ — Dr Zweli Mkhize (@DrZweliMkhize) May 24, 2021 